{meta: title You Are My Treasure}
{meta: artist Jack Greene}
{meta: composer Cindy Walker}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]You are my treasure and my darling I [G7]possess
The world's greater [Am]treasure the treasure of [G7]happiness
Your [F]smiles are my pearls and your ruby [E7]lips are beyond [Am]compare
Your eyes are my [D7]diamonds and my gold is the gold in your [G7]hair
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
Earth has its [C]treasure of fabulous wealth [G7]untold
And who can [Am]measure the treasure the oceans [G7]hold
But [F]whether it be [E7]underneath the sea or the sky [Am]above
[G7]There is no [C]treasure like the [G7]treasure of your [C]love
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
recitation:
There was a time when I thought I could find
Happiness in silver and gold
And I longed for fame and worldly acclaim
And I've hungered for these things filled my very soul
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
But then you came along and now I know I was wrong
For in your eyes I can see
The greatest treasure in all the world
The treasure of your love for me
{end_of_verse}

